{
  "texts": [
    "The first cGAN architecture to generate synthetic Computed Tomography (sCT) to Magnetic Resonance Images (MRI) was proposed by Emami et al.",
    "Unlike standard GAN, both the G and D of cGAN perceive the input image dataset.",
    "This approach tends to be more accurate as compared to previous approaches.",
    "Unlike standard GAN, several studies have been proposed to include SE-ResNet (41, 43), U-Net (44, 45, 57), DenseNet (46) and Embedded Net (26) as Generator for the cGANs.",
    "Evaluation of all four G, Embedded Net, DenseNet, SE ResNet and U-Net in cGAN is proposed by Fetty et al."
  ]
}